    <briefdescription>
<para>Micro-Controller Sleep API. </para>    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is the interface to common MCU sleep management functionality</para><para>The invoking application shall be able to block the system from entering into certain energy modes.</para><para>Sleep modes can be blocked or unblocked by a nested counting semaphore. A block operation increases the counter by one element, unblocking will decrease this.</para><para>The MCU_Sleep_GoSleep will go into the lowest/deepest acceptable sleep mode.</para><para>Pre-sleep and post-sleep callbacks can be registered in order to do the last preparations from the application/BSP perspective before and after sleeping</para><para>Such callbacks might include pin-settings configuration, turning interrupts on/off, etc.</para><para><simplesect kind="warning"><para>Only power-saving modes which retain CPU and RAM are considered here as a sleep mode. This excludes some shutdown-modes! </para></simplesect>
</para>    </detaileddescription>
